{"questionId":"27965","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Six restaurant locations (labelled <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>C</mtext></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>D</mtext></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>E</mtext></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>F</mtext></math>) are shown, together with their Voronoi&nbsp;diagram. All distances are measured in kilometres.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/acc0315b5119f8e934ef7f20a3ae6df2c39a32af.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Restaurant <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>C</mtext></math> is at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>)</mo></math> and restaurant <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>D</mtext></math> is at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Restaurant <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext></math> is at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>)</mo></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Hence find</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>the distance of this point from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>D</mtext></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>their correct substitution into distance formula&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><msup><mfenced><mrow